    • Constructor Detail

      • Trade

        public Trade(java.lang.String username1,
             java.lang.String username2,
             Item[] itemsInvolved,
             boolean isPermanent,
             int tradeId)
        Creates a Trade instance with initiator username1, responder username2, a pair of items involved in the trade itemsInvolved, whether the trade is permanent or not isPermanent, and a unique identifier tradeId. Initially, no meeting is assigned, status of trade is "notStarted". isEvaluate is false

        Precondition: username1 and username2 are valid. tradeId is not negative. the second slot of itemsInvolved, which contains item lend by responder, is not null. trade has to be either a permanent trade or temporary trade.

        Parameters:
        username1 - the username of user that is the initiator of the trade
        username2 - the username of user that is the responder of the trade.
        itemsInvolved - a pair of Items involved in this trade. Contain one or two items.
        isPermanent - a boolean that is true if the trade is permanent, false if it is temporary.
        tradeId - a unique identifier of trade.
